it's only used with no name 
used to instanciate only one object !

define and instanciate the object in the same time !

can either extend any other class
or implemenet an interface !

// this is the normal case !
Animal newAnimal = new Animal();

// this is the inner anonymous case!
Animal anonAnimal = new Animal(){
	public void makeNoise(){
		sout("overriding this method !");
	}
}


// this is case for the interface !
Runnable myAnonymousRunnable = new Runnable(){
	@Override
	public void run(){
		
	}
};
